922
00:42:32,090 --> 00:42:34,860
For example, the common fire hydrant box.

923
00:42:35,070 --> 00:42:36,710
It's everywhere,

924
00:42:36,710 --> 00:42:39,570
but can you use it well?

925
00:42:39,570 --> 00:42:40,660
During a fire,

926
00:42:40,870 --> 00:42:43,470
we have to first open the box

927
00:42:43,470 --> 00:42:44,940
and take out the water hose.

928
00:42:44,940 --> 00:42:47,630
Connect the two ends of the hose

929
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:49,650
to the water outlet and the spray gun.

930
00:42:49,650 --> 00:42:52,250
Pull the hose to where the fire is,

931
00:42:52,250 --> 00:42:54,810
turn on the water supply,

932
00:42:54,810 --> 00:42:55,950
and put out the fire.

933
00:42:56,490 --> 00:42:58,850
But there is one thing

934
00:42:58,850 --> 00:42:59,730
you must be careful of.

935
00:43:00,060 --> 00:43:01,870
If the circuit is on fire,

936
00:43:01,870 --> 00:43:04,050
we have to cut off the power first

937
00:43:04,340 --> 00:43:07,080
before spraying water at the burning object.
